<span id="freeTextContainer378781524330423249">This book is set during the Roman occupation of what was to become part of England and the author decided on a noir approach. Noir and I get along about 50% of the time. And about 50% of this book had the noir flavor. That could have meant I would love it but unfortunately that just wasn&apos;t the case. The (of course) heart-stoppingly beautiful dame was the most noir element of the book. She fit the type really well except at the very end. For the rest of it, feelings got in the way of the noir. At</span>
  <span id="freeText378781524330423249" style="display:none">This book is set during the Roman occupation of what was to become part of England and the author decided on a noir approach. Noir and I get along about 50% of the time. And about 50% of this book had the noir flavor. That could have meant I would love it but unfortunately that just wasn't the case. The (of course) heart-stoppingly beautiful dame was the most noir element of the book. She fit the type really well except at the very end. For the rest of it, feelings got in the way of the noir. At times this book seemed to want to be a romance. It just didn't come together enough for me.</span>
