<div id="review_75566366" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/75566366" />
    <a title="Mary" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2872546-mary"><img alt="Mary" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1256370838p2/2872546.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/75566366?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mary" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mary" href="/user/show/2872546-mary">Mary</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2872546-mary?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2872546-mary?shelf=historical-mystery">historical-mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2872546-mary?shelf=arcturus">arcturus</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2872546-mary?shelf=ancient-rome">ancient-rome</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2872546-mary?shelf=roman-britain">roman-britain</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer75566366" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11159730765181857509">The blurbs on the book cover present this &quot;Roman noir&quot; as a new genre, but it doesn&apos;t seem all that different to me from the early Falco novels by Lindsey Davis or the Libertus novels by Rosemary Rowe. If you like those, you&apos;ll probably like this.<br/><br/>The central mystery is fairly interesting, as are the presumably recurring characters in the household of Arcturus. However, I feel the personal stories of Arcturus and his household were tied up a little too neatly at the end.</span>
  <span id="freeText11159730765181857509" style="display:none">The blurbs on the book cover present this "Roman noir" as a new genre, but it doesn't seem all that different to me from the early Falco novels by Lindsey Davis or the Libertus novels by Rosemary Rowe. If you like those, you'll probably like this.<br /><br />The central mystery is fairly interesting, as are the presumably recurring characters in the household of Arcturus. However, I feel the personal stories of Arcturus and his household were tied up a little too neatly at the end.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11159730765181857509" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

