<div id="review_104219036" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/104219036" />
    <a title="Nancy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/69448-nancy"><img alt="Nancy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1195245293p2/69448.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/104219036?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nancy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nancy" href="/user/show/69448-nancy">Nancy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer104219036" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10223730731735964553">This is a first novel as well as the first book in a new series. I met Kelli Stanley at Bouchercon last year and was intrigued by the concept of &quot;Roman noir.&quot; Stanley set her noir mystery in Roman Britain in the 1st century A.D. Like Jeri Westerson&apos;s Crispin Guest series, Nox Dormienda works because noir fiction is more about characters and atmosphere than it is about a specific culture or historical time period. </span>
  <span id="freeText10223730731735964553" style="display:none">This is a first novel as well as the first book in a new series. I met Kelli Stanley at Bouchercon last year and was intrigued by the concept of "Roman noir." Stanley set her noir mystery in Roman Britain in the 1st century A.D. Like Jeri Westerson's Crispin Guest series, Nox Dormienda works because noir fiction is more about characters and atmosphere than it is about a specific culture or historical time period. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10223730731735964553" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


