<div id="review_1242570752" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1242570752" />
    <a title="Meg" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4254125-meg"><img alt="Meg" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1242570752?book_show_action=true">Mar 31, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Meg" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Meg" href="/user/show/4254125-meg">Meg</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11515437-nox-dormienda">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1242570752" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13426380904440832776"><strong>A very solid historical mystery of Roman Britain. Worth reading!</strong><br/><br/>Recommended. Although this attempt at &quot;Ancient Roman Noir&quot; doesn&apos;t fully pull off its Noir aspirations (not enough quest allegory; city is not a full character, and the women have too many redeeming features for classic noir!), that doesn&apos;t get in the way of it being a great historical mystery and a darned fun read. </span>
  <span id="freeText13426380904440832776" style="display:none"><strong>A very solid historical mystery of Roman Britain. Worth reading!</strong><br /><br />Recommended. Although this attempt at "Ancient Roman Noir" doesn't fully pull off its Noir aspirations (not enough quest allegory; city is not a full character, and the women have too many redeeming features for classic noir!), that doesn't get in the way of it being a great historical mystery and a darned fun read. </span>
